JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 133
EP  - 135
VL  - 7
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In reading an article by Armstrong (1980) the present author misinterpreted the paper, falling victim to Armstrong's hoax. This incident dramatizes how readers are compelled to rely on objective reporting, and raises questions about an advocacy approach to science, an approach promoted by Mitroff and criticized by Armstrong. It is argued here that a distinction must be made: advocacy is useful in conducting research but impartiality is required in reporting research.
AB  - In reading an article by Armstrong (1980) the present author misinterpreted the paper, falling victim to Armstrong's hoax. This incident dramatizes how readers are compelled to rely on objective reporting, and raises questions about an advocacy approach to science, an approach promoted by Mitroff and criticized by Armstrong. It is argued here that a distinction must be made: advocacy is useful in conducting research but impartiality is required in reporting research.
